'''Third Person View''' is a desktop feature that allows users to switch their perspective from their avatar's point of view to a zoomed-out view. It was initially released as a [[VRC+]] Early Access feature and was later made free for all users.

== Controls ==
When enabled, users can adjust the distance from their avatar and switch between behind-the-back view and free rotation.
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Button !! Description
|-
| '''F5'''|| ''Toggles Third Person View''
|-
| '''Scrollwheel'''|| ''Adjusts the distance from the avatar''
|-
| '''TAB'''|| ''Enabled free rotate mode''
|-
|'''ALT + Scrollwheel'''
|''Allows distancing items''
|}

== Settings ==
The following settings can be adjusted in ''Main Menu -> Settings -> Graphics''.
{| class="wikitable"
|+
!Name
!Tooltip
|-
|'''Third Person View'''
|''See VRChat from behind your avatar! Toggle with F5, freely rotate with TAB, and adjust distance using mouse-wheel.''
|-
|'''Third Person View Distance'''
|''Sets the maximum distance the third person viewpoint can extend away from your avatar when third person view is active.''
|-
|'''Third Person View Horizontal'''
|''Sets the abscissa position for the third person viewpoint relative to your avatar.''
|-
|'''Third Person View Vertical'''
|''Sets the ordered position for the third person viewpoint relative to your avatar.''
|-
|'''Vertical Field of View'''
|''Sets the depth position for the third person viewpoint relative to your avatar.''
|}